            <div class="swim-exercises">
                <h2>Types of Swimming Exercises</h2>
                <p>At FIT-TRACK, we offer a variety of swimming workouts:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Freestyle:</strong> Great for overall conditioning.</li>
                    <li><strong>Breaststroke:</strong> Builds strength and endurance.</li>
                    <li><strong>Backstroke:</strong> Improves flexibility and posture.</li>
                    <li><strong>Butterfly:</strong> A challenging full-body workout.</li>
                    <li><strong>Water Aerobics:</strong> Fun and effective low-impact exercise.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="swim-benefits">
                <h2>Benefits of Swimming</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Full-body workout that builds strength and endurance</li>
                    <li>Low-impact exercise that is easy on the joints</li>
                    <li>Improves cardiovascular health</li>
                    <li>Enhances flexibility and range of motion</li>
                    <li>Can be a relaxing and enjoyable activity</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="swim-exercises-list">
                <h2>Basic Swimming Exercises</h2>

                <div class="swim-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/SWIMMING/freestyle.jpg" alt="Freestyle">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>1. Freestyle</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Start in the water, face down.<br>
                            Alternate your arms in a windmill motion while kicking your legs.<br>
                            Breathe by turning your head to the side.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Great for overall conditioning and endurance.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="swim-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/SWIMMING/breaststroke.jpg" alt="Breaststroke">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>2. Breaststroke</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Start in the water, face down.<br>
                            Pull your arms back in a circular motion while kicking your legs.<br>
                            Breathe by lifting your head out of the water.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Builds strength and endurance; good for beginners.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="swim-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/SWIMMING/backstroke.jpg" alt="Backstroke">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>3. Backstroke</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Lie on your back in the water.<br>
                            Alternate your arms in a windmill motion while kicking your legs.<br>
                            Keep your head back and eyes up.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Improves flexibility and posture; great for relaxation.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="swim-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/SWIMMING/butterfly.jpg" alt="Butterfly">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>4. Butterfly</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Start in the water, face down.<br>
                            Move both arms simultaneously in a circular motion while kicking your legs together.<br>
                            Breathe by lifting your head out of the water.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Challenging full-body workout; builds strength and coordination.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="swim-exercise">
                    <img src="/image/assets/SWIMMING/water aerobics.jpg" alt="Water Aerobics">
                    <div class="exercise-description">
                        <h3>5. Water Aerobics</h3>
                        <h4>How to do it:</h4>
                        <p>
                            Participate in a structured class or follow a routine in the water.<br>
                            Use movements like jumping jacks, leg lifts, and arm circles.
                        </p>
                        <h4>Benefits:</h4>
                        <p>Fun and effective low-impact exercise; great for all fitness levels.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

